Bucket.documentation: The S3 bucket used to send the request. This is an optional parameter that will be set automatically for operations that are scoped to an S3 bucket.

Region.documentation: The AWS region used to dispatch the request.

UseFIPS.documentation: When true, send this request to the FIPS-compliant regional endpoint. If the configured endpoint does not have a FIPS compliant endpoint, dispatching the request will return an error.

UseDualStack.documentation: When true, use the dual-stack endpoint. If the configured endpoint does not support dual-stack, dispatching the request MAY return an error.

Endpoint.documentation: Override the endpoint used to send this request

ForcePathStyle.documentation: When true, force a path-style endpoint to be used where the bucket name is part of the path.

Accelerate.documentation: When true, use S3 Accelerate. NOTE: Not all regions support S3 accelerate.

UseGlobalEndpoint.documentation: Whether the global endpoint should be used, rather then the regional endpoint for us-east-1.

UseObjectLambdaEndpoint.documentation: Internal parameter to use object lambda endpoint for an operation (eg: WriteGetObjectResponse)

Key.documentation: The S3 Key used to send the request. This is an optional parameter that will be set automatically for operations that are scoped to an S3 Key.

Prefix.documentation: The S3 Prefix used to send the request. This is an optional parameter that will be set automatically for operations that are scoped to an S3 Prefix.

CopySource.documentation: The Copy Source used for Copy Object request. This is an optional parameter that will be set automatically for operations that are scoped to Copy Source.

DisableAccessPoints.documentation: Internal parameter to disable Access Point Buckets

DisableMultiRegionAccessPoints.documentation: Whether multi-region access points (MRAP) should be disabled.

UseArnRegion.documentation: When an Access Point ARN is provided and this flag is enabled, the SDK MUST use the ARN's region when constructing the endpoint instead of the client's configured region.

UseS3ExpressControlEndpoint.documentation: Internal parameter to indicate whether S3Express operation should use control plane, (ex. CreateBucket)

DisableS3ExpressSessionAuth.documentation: Parameter to indicate whether S3Express session auth should be disabled
